outputs.output_descr: The project aims to extend the UNV/UNDP assistance to the Government of South Africa to enable efficient delivery of health care services in the Limpopo Province.  UNDP and UNV will provide medical doctors to facilitate the delivery of health services to the public.  The project also aims to increase the retention rate of medical doctors and interns who have served their specialization studies in the Province;  Improve quality and quantity of service delivery of medical services in the province; and enhance commitment of local doctors to serve in disadvantaged areas as a result of increased appreciation of volunteerism.

project_descr: UNV SUPPORT TO THE HEALTH SECTOR IN RURAL AREAS
